news.title: Nashik: Over 1,000 building plans await approval from town planning department
news.para: Municipal commissioner Manisha Khatri, in order to streamline the building plan proposal submission and spped up the approval process, made the online process mandatory and discontinued the offline system.

news.title: Budget 2025: Private investment needs a boost, real estate sector can be the catalyst
news.para: ​Simplification of input tax credit mechanism will help lowering down the cost of construction and will help in development of investible grade assets, which can be lucrative to the private equity sector.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body to now issue 15-day notice before a demolition drive
news.para: According to the rules, property owners must receive a show-cause notice via registered post at least 15 days before any action, or within the timeframe specified by local municipal laws, whichever is longer.

news.title: Nagpur civic body to mop up Rs 235 crore property tax in 60 days
news.para: The sluggish pace of tax recovery forced NMC to take a Rs 500 crore loan to meet its share of funding for various state and central govt-backed infrastructure projects.

news.title: About 1.38 lakh real estate projects registered under RERA across India: Economic Survey
news.para: According to the Economic Survey 2024-25, about 1.38 lakh complaints have been disposed of by the RERA across the country.

news.title: Lucknow development body to inspect all commercial buildings
news.para: LDA will carry out citywide inspections to identify unauthorised construction and ensure adherence to safety regulations.

news.title: Maharashtra government proposes new sand mining policy
news.para: In Feb 2024, the state govt came up with a proposal to set up sand depots in every tehsil, to be overseen by the local revenue official and to provide sand on a no-profit, no-loss basis.

news.title: Kolkata: Flat owners block KMC's attempt to raze building on Christopher Road
news.para: The KMC buildings department decided to start the demolition of the under construction building from Thursday, reportedly after conducting a survey of both buildings that have been resting against one another.

news.title: Jaipur: Sand crisis worsens as govt fails to auction mining leases
news.para: According to official documents, the only operational mining leases are in Todaraisingh, Kekri, Asind, Rashmi, Jaitaran, Khetri, Sarwar, and Sirohi.

news.title: Mumbai civic body plans to halve city’s debris waste collection fee
news.para: Mumbai produces 8,500 tonnes of construction and demolition (C&D) waste daily, but BMC's two collection facilities in Dahisar and Shilphata, which began operations last year, are working at half their capacity.

news.title: Trichy corporation boost property tax collection, targets 90% by March
news.para: Apart from improving routine property tax collection including arrear demands, the local body surveyed more than 5,400 properties and added Rs10 crore to its kitty by addressing lapses in tax assessments.

news.title: Nashik civic body sets February 28 deadline for property tax objections
news.para: There are around 5.6 lakh properties registered with the property tax department of the Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC). The civic administration has made available a "property registry" in each of the six divisional offices of the NMC.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT's net operating income up 11% in Q3 FY25
news.para: The board of directors of Brookprop Management Services, the manager of Brookfield India REIT, have declared distribution of Rs 2,977.98 million/Rs 4.90 per unit for the quarter ended December 31, 2024.

news.title: Equinox India Developments raises Rs 950 crore
news.para: Corporate guarantee in favour of IDBI Trusteeship Services, towards the due and punctual payment and discharge of the other debenture obligations being issued /to be issued by LLDL.

news.title: TCS to invest Rs 690 crore to set up 37-acre campus in Kochi
news.para: The Mumbai-headquartered software behemoth will invest Rs 690 crore on this project, the proposal on which the government mentions the purpose as electronics R&D and IT/ITeS.

news.title: Mumbai: Dharavi residents resisting eligibility survey face warning
news.para: In a press release issued on Thursday, the NMDPL stated that so far it covered 80,000 tenements. Posters have been put up in lanes, societies, and tenements where people have been resisting the survey.

news.title: Panasonic Life Solutions India acquires 6,586.90 sq meters land in Mumbai for Rs 160 crore
news.para: The land, spanning approximately 6,586.90 sq meters (about 7,877.87 sq yards), was acquired by Panasonic Life Solutions India from River Rose Developers LLP, as per IGR property registration documents.

news.title: Blackstone in talks to buy stake in New York City office building: Sources
news.para: The planned move comes as Blackstone executives signaled on an earnings call earlier in the day that the troubled commercial real estate sector was stabilizing.

news.title: Delhi: Birla Cotton Mills to be redeveloped into residential mixed-use project
news.para: All the partners will jointly develop 30 lakh square feet of housing and retail space on this land parcel owned by Saroj Kumar Poddar-led Adventz Group firm Texmaco Infrastructure and Holdings.

news.title: Ajmera Realty acquires 1,341.1 sq meter land in Mumbai for Rs 51 crore
news.para: Ajmera Realty & Infra India acquired the land through a competitive bidding process from Karamshi Jethabhai Somaiya Trust at a cost of Rs 51 crore.
